            <h1 class="text-center mb-2">What is a Pool Game or Billiards?</h1>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <img src="https://www.livesnooker.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/2H7REBT-scaled.jpg" width="400">
        <p style="color: wheat">The <b style="color: white">Pool Game</b> is a classification of cue sports played on a table with six pockets along the rails, into which balls are deposited. Each specific pool game has its own name; some of the better-known include the <b style="color: white">eight-ball</b>, the <b style="color: white">blackball</b> and the <b style="color: white">nine-ball</b>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="container">
        <img src="https://media.istockphoto.com/photos/group-of-friends-shooting-pool-on-a-night-out-picture-id537121337?b=1&k=20&m=537121337&s=170667a&w=0&h=lMdYk86ZjE5cT4MoVgsOcMMBttaLhwixReIDXijVugE=" width="400">
        <p style="color: yellow">The pool game is a two-player (or two-team) game using a standard billiards table and cues.</p>
      </div>

        <h2><b style="color: pink">The 3 types of games…</b></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="container">
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/96/Eight_Ball_Rack_2005_SeanMcClean.jpg" width="400">
      <p style="color:white">The <b style="color:black">8-Ball</b> is a call shot game <b style="color: black">played</b> with a <b style="color: black">cue ball</b> (white ball) and 15 object <b style="color: black">balls</b>, numbered 1 through 15. One <b style="color: black">player</b> must pocket <b style="color: black">balls</b> of the group numbered 1 through 7 (solid colors), while the other player has 9 through 15 (stripes). The player pocketing either group first, and then legally pocketing the <b style="color: black">8-ball</b> at last wins the game.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="container">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="400">
        <p style="color: white">The <b>Blackball</b> is a game <b>played</b> with a <b>cue ball</b> (white ball) with seven red balls (reds), seven yellow balls (yellows) and one black ball (the 8-ball). One <b>player</b> must pocket <b>balls</b> of the group colour (reds or yellows). The <b>player</b> pocketing either group first, and then legally pocketing the <b>8-ball</b>, at last, wins the game. It is slightly the same as the <b>8-ball game</b>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="container">
        <img src="https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/pool-balls-table-2718913.jpg" width="400">
        <p style="color: white">The <b style="color: yellow">9-ball</b> is completely different from the two above. This type of game is <b>played</b> with <b>nine object balls</b> numbered one through <b>nine</b> and a <b>cue ball</b>. If a <b>player</b> pockets <b>any ball</b> on a legal shot, he remains at the table for another shot, and continues until he misses, fouls, or wins the game by pocketing the <b>9-ball</b>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="container">
        <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcT3hOOSXrWyYfI6HbH-8ya7GmWeC9ByC6GygA&usqp=CAU" width="400">
        <h2><b style="color:red">Before starting a game…</b></h2>
        <p style="color: grey">Among the three worldwide games mentioned before, the <b>Blackball</b> is mostly practised in Mauritius. There are series of rules and regulations you need to know before starting a game:</p>
        <li style="color: white">how to rack the balls</li>
        <li style="color: white">how to play the game</li>
        <li style="color: white">how to position you hands while playing</li>
        <li style="color: white">how to avoid making fouls during the play</li>
      </div>
